This bug is quite insane. The same code runs [`onDrag`](https://github.com/Thibaut/devdocs/blob/ddf87bb0b8749fd5366ce850009880d85b7749d1/assets/javascripts/views/layout/resizer.coffee#L41) and [`onDragEnd`](https://github.com/Thibaut/devdocs/blob/ddf87bb0b8749fd5366ce850009880d85b7749d1/assets/javascripts/views/layout/resizer.coffee#L49). Both read the cursor position from `event.pageX` but somehow `onDragEnd` ends up writing a different value, when it should always be the same as the last `onDrag` value (which is what I get on all the browsers I've tested). I even added a check that the `dragend` value is within 5px of the last `drag` value a [couple weeks ago](https://github.com/Thibaut/devdocs/commit/c2a20ef5863081aca00003bde4d50deca1a139a8).

